ls : list files
ls -a : list all files (hidden files also ) [only works in git bash]
ls -Force : same as ls -a for vs code
git clone link : to copy from github (remote) to local
git status 
git add file name
git add . : saves all new or modified files
git commit -m "message"
git push origin main : to push local repo to remote repo or github
git push -u origin main [-u sets upstream so that furthure only git push is sufficient to push]

#INIT COMMANDS

git init : make a git repo
git remote add origin link
git remote -v : verify remote


#BRANCH COMMANDS

git branch : check bracnch
git branch -M main : rename branch
git checkout branch name : to navigate
git checkout -b new branch name : create new branch 
git checkout -d branch name : delete branch

#MERGING COMMANDS
WAY 1
git diff branch name : to compare commits , branches , files and more 
git merge branch name
WAY 2
Create a PR(Pull Request)

#PULL COMMAND
git pull origin main

#UNDOING CHANGES
1.Staged changes
git reset file name
git reset

2.commited changes (for one commit) 
get reset HEAD~1

3.commited changes (for many commits)
git reset commit hash
